caption: It's a church (and a basilica at that!)---what else can I say? The community was very friendly (without being overbearing), and the homily was wonderful. They used incense at the Mass I attended---if that doesn't work for you, you may want to see what other options are available, but if it does work for you, you should definitely go! I would definitely go back. :)

I really liked this Roman church which is very well designed and very spacious. The atmosphere was warm and welcoming. It is ideally located in the heart of a popular district of Paris. A true place of urban contemplation.

A lively and welcoming chapel, well integrated into the life of the neighborhood with multiple social actions for the elderly, the sick, the homeless, etc. In addition to its history, it has experience and plenty of things to discover. It is possible to visit it so don't hesitate.
